laboratory_examinations.findings: The liver enhances homogeneously without intrahepatic biliary duct dilation. Small hypodensities in segment II and segment VI likely represent small cysts or biliary hamartomas. No suspicious liver lesion identified. Portal and hepatic veins patent. Nondistended gallbladder normal. The spleen is homogeneous and normal in size. The pancreas is without focal lesion. Adrenal glands unremarkable. Kidneys demonstrate symmetric nephrograms with prompt contrast excretion. No focal lesion or hydronephrosis. Stomach moderately distended. Appendix demonstrates wall thickening, adjacent adenopathy, and trace surrounding fat stranding with an appendicolith noted. No drainable fluid collection.
